  "body": "There is a counter to limit the number of announced block for each peer. The counter is increased only when notifying a block from peer. But the counter might be decreased many times when calling `forgetHash`. Why does it need to decrease the counter again when removing hash from `f.fetching`? \r\n\r\n```\r\nfunc (f *Fetcher) forgetHash(hash common.Hash) {\r\n        // Remove all pending announces and decrement DOS counters\r\n        for _, announce := range f.announced[hash] {\r\n                f.announces[announce.origin]--\r\n                if f.announces[announce.origin] == 0 {\r\n                        delete(f.announces, announce.origin)\r\n                }\r\n        }\r\n        delete(f.announced, hash)\r\n        if f.announceChangeHook != nil {\r\n                f.announceChangeHook(hash, false)\r\n        }\r\n        // Remove any pending fetches and decrement the DOS counters\r\n        if announce := f.fetching[hash]; announce != nil {\r\n                f.announces[announce.origin]--\r\n                if f.announces[announce.origin] == 0 {\r\n                        delete(f.announces, announce.origin)\r\n                }\r\n                delete(f.fetching, hash)\r\n        }\r\n       ...\r\n}\r\n```",
